<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.publicdebt.treas.gov/opd/opdfaq.htm#opdfaq33">www.publicdebt.treas.gov/...m#opdfaq33</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
will explain everything you need to know on the national debt.  Intragovernmental holdings, make up the difference between the Debt held by the public figure as reported by the CBO, and that from your treasury figures. IGH are defined here as:<br>
Government Account Series securities held by Government trust funds, revolving funds, and special funds; and Federal Financing Bank  securities. A small amount of marketable securities are held by government accounts.   <br>
<br>
The difference is a key one, as the SS trust fund, and the corresponding increase of the SS tax under Reagan was <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>designed statutorily</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to build up a debt, to eventually be repaid by the government.  Did those holdings grow? Sure.<br>
<br>
